### 12. Mock Data -- Unsplash Image Strategy

For the clothing catalog, use specific Unsplash photo IDs that show clothing items on clean/white backgrounds or on models. The URL format is:

```
https://images.unsplash.com/photo-{ID}?w={width}&q=80&fit=crop
```

Recommended search categories for sourcing IDs:
- Tops: search "white t-shirt flat lay", "blouse fashion", "shirt minimal"
- Bottoms: search "jeans flat lay", "trousers minimal", "pants fashion"
- Dresses: search "dress fashion", "summer dress", "elegant dress"
- Outerwear: search "coat fashion", "blazer minimal", "jacket style"
- Accessories: search "fashion accessories", "bag minimal", "scarf style"

Each item should have 2 URL variants:
- `imageUrl` with `?w=800` for detail/workspace views
- `thumbnailUrl` with `?w=400` for grid cards

For the landing page hero, use a large fashion photography image with `?w=1920`.

